qa_pairs.subject: ComfyUI-Mirror
qa_pairs.question: What does the ComfyUI-Mirror node do?
qa_pairs.answer: The ComfyUI-Mirror node is used to mirror a latent along the Y or X axis. It is best used as part of an img2img workflow.

qa_pairs.subject: ComfyUI-Mirror
qa_pairs.question: Can you provide an example JSON file for ComfyUI-Mirror?
qa_pairs.answer: Yes, an example JSON file can be found here: https://github.com/spro/comfyui-mirror/blob/main/examples/latent-mirror-example.json.

qa_pairs.subject: ComfyUI-Mirror
qa_pairs.question: What are the examples images for ComfyUI-Mirror?
qa_pairs.answer: Example images for ComfyUI-Mirror can be seen here: https://github.com/spro/comfyui-latentmirror/blob/main/examples/example.png?raw=true.

qa_pairs.subject: ComfyUI-Mirror
qa_pairs.question: How can I install ComfyUI-Mirror?
qa_pairs.answer: To install ComfyUI-Mirror, you would clone the repo within `ComfyUI/custom_nodes` and restart and refresh ComfyUI.

qa_pairs.subject: ComfyUI-Mirror
qa_pairs.question: What is the installation command for ComfyUI-Mirror?
qa_pairs.answer: The installation command is: `cd ComfyUI/custom_nodes && git clone https://github.com/spro/comfyui-latentmirror`.
